17/08/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Three infants died in a fire at the Giulesti maternity hospital in Bucharest on Monday (August 16th), while two pregnant women and eight newborns sustained burns. 
The fire was caused by an explosion on the second floor of the hospital. 
Authorities say the thick smoke quickly spread to the intensive care unit where the premature babies were. 
An investigation is under way to determine the cause of the blast. 
(Cotidianul - 17/08/10; AP, Evenimentul Zilei, CNN, Gandul, Ziare, Romania Libera - 16/08/10)
